div1.p: In the Matter of the Application of Soo Hoo Wing, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus for Fue Gam.

Upon reading the foregoing petition, and hearing Mr C.A. Dolph, Mr C.B.Bellinger and Mr Paul R.Deady, of counsel for the petitioner, It is ORDERED that the Clerk of the United States Circuit Court for the District of Washington, file the foregoing petition, and issue a writ of Habeas Corpus thereon as prayef for therein, directed to Woolery, Sheriff of King County, in the State of Washington, commanding him to pro- duce the body of Fue Gam, the person named in said petition, before the Honorable William B. Gilbert, Judge of our Circuit Court of the United States for the District of Washington, at the United States Court Room in the City of Portland, State of Oregon, at ten o'clock in the forenoon of Monday, February 6, 1893, together with the cause of her detention:
In the matter of the application of. - Soo Hoo Wing for Writ of Habeas Corpus
Filed Febu 4 1893 in the U. S. Circuit Court
